default1. Introductiondefault and summarydefault&#xa0;default1.1 defaultThe Royal College of Psychiatrists (RCPsych) is the leading medical authority on mental health in the United Kingdom and is the professional and educational organisation for doctors specialising in psychiatry.
default&#xa0;
default1.2default defaultLiaison psychiatry is the sub-specialty which provides psychiatric treatment to patients attending general hospitals, whether they attend out-patient clinics, accident 
defaultand
default emergency departments or are admitted to in-patient wards.
default&#xa0;
defaultTherefore it
default&#xa0;
defaultdeals with the interface between physical and psychological health.
default&#xa0;
defaultThere is now abundant evidence that medical and surgical patients have a high prevalence of psychiatric disorder which can be effectively treated with psychological or pharmacological methods.
default&#xa0;default1.3default 
defaultOur e
defaultvidence focus
defaultes
default on the interaction between mental health problems
default,
default such as depression and anxiety, and long
default-
defaultterm physical health conditions, and the implications 
defaultof this interaction 
defaultfor individuals, clinicians, healthcare providers and commissioners. This evidence will also be relevant to other issues under consideration by this 
defaultS
defaultelect 
defaultC
defaultommittee, including the location of care for people with long
default-
defaultterm conditions (LTCs) and the integration of care across traditional healthcare boundaries. 
default&#xa0;
default1.4default 
defaultThe issues 
defaultwe 
defaultconsider
default 
defaultinclude:
default&#xa0;
default1)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWhat constitutes a long
default-
defaultterm condition
default2)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe problem of multimorbidity
default3)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWhere is the majority of healthcare for LTCs provided
default?
default4)
